<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-780-508  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 780 508.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  May 29 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>LSI Logic opts for quality upgrade in Japan.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Yazawa, Naoyuki.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   LSI Logic Corp. (quality control).andO;Ticker:    LSI.andO;Topic:     Quality controlSemiconductor industrySupport ServicesMarketingSubsidiary Companies.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>LSI LOGIC OPTS FOR QUALITY UPGRADE IN JAPAN TOKYO, JAPAN, 1990 MAY 21 (NB) --The Japanese subsidiary of U.S.-based semiconductor maker LSI Logic willexpand its business operation rapidly in order to increase the quality of itsproducts and services.andM;As a sales arm of the American firm, the subsidiary has been puttingeverything it's got into sales and marketing, but Japanese clients aredemanding equal quality and service with Japanese makers.andM;LSI currently employs 100 Japanese and plans to hire 40 more Japanese staffmembers this year.andP;  In order to put those new employees on the jobimmediately, it is preparing new educational programs.andM;On the other hand, the subsidiary is making advances over other worldwide LSILogic subsidiaries by developing gate arrays incorporating U.S.-based MIPSComputer's RISC (reduced instruction set computer) architecture.andO;Consequently, research and development is strongly emphasized.andM;The Japanese subsidiary has expanded its business 60 to 100 percent annuallysince it was established in 1984.andP;  It is expecting to achieve 10 billion yenor $66.7 million in sales in fiscal 1992.andM;(Naoyuki Yazawa/19900521/Press Contact: LSI Logic, 03-589-2711)</TEXT></DOC>